I"!<p>Introduction to C# and Java type systems. Links to details are provided for reference.</p>

<p>Both specifications defines how types are declared, used, and managed in the language runtime(<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Virtual_Execution_System">VES</a>, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Java_virtual_machine">JVM</a>) and is also an important part of the runtime’s support for cross-language integration.</p>

<ul>
  <li>Enables type safety and high performant code across platforms and languagues.</li>
  <li>Defines rules that the languague must follow, which ensures objects created in different languagues can intercat with each other.
(<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Visual_Basic_.NET">VB.Net</a> can talk to C# libraries, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Apache_Groovy">Groovy</a> can use Java libraries).</li>
  <li>Provides primitive types used in application development.</li>
</ul>

<p>This topic contains the following sections:</p>

<ul>
  <li><a href="#headTypes">Types</a></li>
  <li><a href="#headDef">Type definitions</a></li>
  <li><a href="#headMem">Type members</a></li>
  <li><a href="#headChar">Characteristics of Type members</a></li>
</ul>

